generalComment.value:
"With reference to the EN 15804:2012+A2:2019 standard, the analysis describes a specific product using specific data for the processes on which the manufacturer of the specific product has an influence:
• All data related to the company's CORE activities and therefore falling within phase A3 were obtained directly from the company's databases and are therefore to be understood as site specific;
• For UPSTREAM data, and therefore linked to phases A1 and A2 (for which the standard provides for the use of generic data), the data for as regards weight, quantity, raw materials and waste, they are derived either from the company databases or from reworkings provided directly by Baraclit S.p.A. and summarized in a ""Data Collection Checklist"", and therefore are to be considered site-specific. The type of material and processes were taken from the Ecoinvent 3.8 database. The steel components are been modeled taking into consideration the % of recycled content declared by the suppliers (considering only the third-party verified environmental claims, such as self-declarations according to ISO 14021 verified by a Third Party and/or EPD) and the incidence of suppliers with respect to the quantities of steel delivered in the reference year;
• The DOWNSTREAM data of phase A5 were processed from primary data supplied by Baraclit and are therefore to be considered specific.

Site-specific data refer to the year 2021.

As regards the quality of the electrical and thermal energy data, the company procures itself through the energy system and from the photovoltaic system located on the roof of the factory. For the portion of energy withdrawn from the grid, the Italian Residual Energy Mix 2021 (Source AIB) is considered, while for self-consumed energy from photovoltaics, the Ecoinvent dataset Electricity, low voltage {IT}| electricity production, photovoltaic, 3kWp slanted-roof installation, multi-Si, panel, mounted | Cutoff, U. Gas consumption is modeled with the dataset Heat, district or industrial, natural gas {Europe without Switzerland}|heat production, natural gas, at industrial furnace >100kW | Cutoff, U."


The allocation was made on a linear meter basis.


"For the study in question, the following were considered as cut-offs:
• Galvanizing of the auxiliary material used in the production of the “Painting lamella set” (22,72 kg, to be allocated on linear metres);
• Galvanizing of the material added during installation “Hilti screw HUS4” (0,15 kg) and “Seismic set M16” (0,19 kg).
Considering the % weight of these components on the total weight of Aliant products, which is <0.004%, the relative environmental impact throughout the product life cycle."

technologyDescriptionAndIncludedProcesse.value:
"Aliant is available in various types, depending on the structural capacity of the project request, and with an important variability of lengths extending to over 30m of light.
Furthermore, Aliant is available for each length and type of capacity in three different versions from the point of view of thermal performance: Klima Plus, Klima Max and Klima Top."

technologicalApplicability.value:
"Aliant is the company's unique ""wing"" roofing element. The element has a monolithic structure made of prestressed reinforced concrete (c.a.p.) and a cross-sectional box, inside which the insulating material is encapsulated. This results in excellent structural and thermal performance.
Another notable feature of Aliant is its ""pre-finished"" monoblock characteristic: Aliant modules come out of the Baraclit production plant already insulated, painted on the intrados, and waterproofed, eliminating the need for further work on-site."
